  "unit": {
    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Approved. 36 vocab + 60 grammar, full chain with pilot rigor. Stage-7 calibration hardened 3 systemic validators (V-5 own-multiword-headword exemption, V-8 copula skip, V-13 bare \"going to\" is everyday English not a tense name); 6 audited level-grants for the unit's \"More irregular verbs\" box (buy/bought, know/knew, made, wrote). Verify took 2 rounds: round 1 fixed mc.003/mc.001 plausible-correct distractors, gf.001/002 polarity strict, the anagram-prompt grammar terms, and ec.003's clunky compound; round 2 caught \"mark\" (untaught, masked by the name \"Mark\") in to-fail and tf.001's missing uncontracted negative — all fixed. Stage-8 adjudication: all 11 glosses correct + genuinely above level (level-gloss r2), all 42 translations accurate both directions (translation r2 + read), F54 \"Sie\"=\"She\" subject. Grammar set is textbook-faithful (the 4 box verbs, Did/Was-Were rule, why-because) across 10 formats, difficulties 1–3, du-form hints with allowed German pedagogical terms. rejectRate target < 5%."
  },
